caption: My husband and I and another couple had the pleasure of finding The Black Jockey on our first night and first visit to Louisville. We were welcomed by Queen, who, even though she was wearing a mask, I could tell, was smiling. Daniel waited on us and was so kind and engaging.  Haley, the chef, came out to speak to us. We were glad we could could compliment her in person on the meal.  Everything we ordered was delicious.  Our next visit from Georgia will definitely include a trip back to The Black Jockey . . .

As soon as we walked in the door my husband and I was greeted by the Owner, Ms. Tawana Bain, who gave us a warm welcome and directed us to our table. The ambiance & atmosphere was inviting, the decor was elegant and fitting for the theme of the restaurant, and the food (I had shrimp & grits) was DELISH! I salute

The food was decent, but the service was not. The manager tried to blame the bad service on young employees; I guess he thinks our server, who was no less than 45, is young. I'm actually surprised I'm still not waiting for the check.

We stopped by before going to the palace and the experience was not good. They only served a bar Manu at 6 o'clock on a Saturday night. We waited about 15 mins for a server to show up and then another 25 minutes before getting our drink we ordered. The fish sliders are basically the same ones you buy at Walmart frozen. They are even the same trapezoid shape. We finally got our a bill after being there an hour and 15 minutes and paid for our meal BEFORE even getting it. We had to take it in to go boxes and eat while waiting in line for the event at the palace. Not sure how this place is still open.

We arrived at 6:30 to learn they were only serving a bar menu. We were seeing a show at the Palace and expected the restaurant to be ready for a crowd since they are directly across from the venue.  After 30 minutes of waiting at out table and watching many people walk out, the only server comes to tell me the drink I ordered was made wrong and will be brought to me shortly. At 7:10 we received the chicken tenders and fish sliders we ordered 30 minutes prior. I had asked the server to just pack them in to go containers as we needed to get in line for the show. The drinks were over priced and the amount of time we waited for "appetizers" was unacceptable.

I've been there twice to have a drink and something to eat before a show at the Palace.  Both times the service was extremely slow... like waiting in line at the DMV slow.  Food is mediocre at best. Last time, we waited about five minutes to be acknowledged by a server who walked past us about 3 times first. Then waited a few more minutes before she stopped at our table so we could place a drink order. We told the server we wanted to order food also. 10 minutes later, still no drinks or menus, the server said our drinks would be right up. After another 5 minutes of waiting, we got up and left. We wasted over 20 minutes here for nothing. I could tell that other people were getting really annoyed as well. It was early, so it wasn't that busy, but there was only one server and a bartender, both of whom had no sense of urgency. I've never seen a bartender move that slow. There are way too many other options in the area. I won't be back.

Lady at the door was warm and friendly tonight. The gentleman checking ID's said they was still serving food. We sat down and the server came over 10 mins in and ask us did we need anything we ask for food items and she immediately told us the kitchen is closed and beought out 3 plates a little while after. Never going again. $10 to get in and I can't order food
This is the spot! DJ plus an amazing live cover band! A must do for Louisville night life. Especially if you are 30 and up

They were absolutely delicious! Cynthia waited on us and was terrific!!  And it’s literally right across the street from the Palace. Fun and convenient! Give it a go!

They were out of 4 beers on tap, they couldn’t find the menus, the music kept get interrupted by text notification tones and once a full blown call was received so when the music stopped instead of a text tone when the music stopped it was the ringing of a phone and it was super loud!! They need real music and not a playlist on someones personal phone. We would see the phone light up across the bar when it happened too. The kicker for us was there no soap in restroom!

Great spot...went on a Saturday to hear a jazz band and they were amazing, not to mention the drinks were spot on. Service was good as well, nice place to check out for a nice evening. Food menu small but still tasty!

Had some delicious small plates (try the bacon stuffed tots!) which was just right before we went to the concert. She whipped up some fantastic cocktails and was excellent company while we were there.

The food here is okay. Not spectacular but definitely  worth stopping  in to try. The sweet tea is not always very sweet so it depends how you like it. Service is good. The prices are decent and  fair for what you are getting as well.
Service is good, but they need to work on their air conditioning. It is stifling in there sometimes. Food is good but kinda pricey depending on if you get lunch or dinner menu.
Great bartenders, decent food and drinks. Happy hour is fantastic.

it took almost 45 minutes for our first drinks to come out. Very slow service as the place wasnt even half full. Understaffed and the servers they did have weren't friendly. The food was average at best and multiple food orders were incorrect. I definitely wouldn't recommend this place as there as TONS of better options around. I'll be surprised if this place is still open under current management in a year.

Service sucked...waited hour on potatoes never came..fish was nasty overpriced...absolutely won't be back...get Bill prices higher than menu stated....rip off..50 bucks for fish sandwich and 5 beers...beware

My partner and I attempted to try this establishment on Saturday, however the door was locked despite the fact there were many patrons inside. A gentleman approached us on the sidewalk and said, "oh, go back to the door and 'he' will let you in." So we did as he suggested, only to be greeted by a very rude guy working inside, as he approached the door and turned us away with no explanation, meanwhile allowing the gentleman who suggested for us to go to the door to go in. The guy working there looked him up and down then said, "But he can come in". How rude and discriminatory is that? Very! It was apparent that he had interest in the gentleman, therefore letting him in, but denying us because we are females. Tacky and we will never spend one cent there. We probably should not have even considered the place after our friends already had such a terrible experience there earlier in the night. Out of convenience we attempted and did not succeed. We walked away saving money and laughing at the joke of a worker we were presented with.
Cool venue with a lot of space close to music venues.

Fabulous place with theeeee best cocktails!!! Beautiful decor and a VIP booth that looks like something out of the movies! Location is great too.  Hit this place up before a concert at the Mercury or the Palace to save a ton on alcohol.  The owners are amazing  and staff were friendly and attentive!  Looking forward to going back soon!
Nice setup but over priced and the food is not good. To many choices that are 3 Stars better and at the same price.
Can't say enough good about this place. The owner and staff were great! Can't wait to go back. Thoroughly enjoyed ourselves.

The dining area is nice and there's a huge window where you can see The Louisville Palace. Nice servers. Huge bar. But that's where it ends. There were 5 of us and no one was impressed with anything they ate. The food, honestly, wasn't memorable and there wasn't much of a selection. A sandwich, a green salad, chicken salad, no steak or real entree like what you imagine if you were really going to dinner. Average or below. My bacon burger was just a standard burger, very eh, and over cooked, but how can you not overcook a 1/3" thick patty? My daughter had wings, nothing special, and slightly rubbery. I left feeling underwhelmed and disappointed. If it were a quick lunch spot it would be fine I guess, but for dinner? Nope. It's a shame because they could do a lot with such a nice space. In the meantime, Qdoba is down the street.
Best damn bourbon dipping sauce. Live music, and the staff is fantastic

Nice bar and restaurant with good food. Looks very nice inside and employees uplifting! 👍 The Palace and Mercury Ballroom directly across the street with plenty entertainment on regular basis

Stopped by over the weekend of 2/24 while waiting for a ride and had a couple of drinks that were AMAZING! David, the bartender/mixologist was very pleasant and cool to talk to! Would have ordered food but not enough time. Will return for dinner and MORE drinks.
Great service!!!   Great Happy Hour!

My husband and I had dinner last night before a show across the street at the Palace. Walking into the restaurant it looks nice. It was busy but not crazy busy. We told our waitress after she took our drink order and took a little longer than usual to get them to the table that we were going to a show and we were hoping to get through dinner a little faster than normal to which she huffed and took our order. Twenty five minutes later we asked another worker, I’m assuming he was a manager, if we would get the salad before the dinner came. He walked around the corner and immediately came walking back with the salad. Clearly it had been ready and just sitting. Approximately 45 minutes later our food came. My dish (risotto) was inedible. My husband even tried it and said how awful it tasted. He ate his (pork and risotto) but later confessed it almost made him gag while eating it. I tried it and thought it wasn’t much better than mine and the pork was clearly not cooked right. Not one time did our waitress check on us or ask if everything was ok. When we had our second round of drinks while waiting for something to come to the table it was only because my husband called for her as she walked by. Terrible experience!
This place is beyond foul. WILL NEVER GO BACK! Don't waste your money. Absolutely disgusting. Food presentation was awful and less then mediocre. Tasteless and WAY too expensive.
Food was okay but not worth the price. Our burger was overcooked and dry. $16 for a cheese plate with 4 pieces of cheese... I don't think so

I give this restaurant the highest rating because of their impeccable service and their delicious food.  They serve American fare with a southern flair! As soon as you walk through the door you are immediately put at ease with the staff’s hospitality and friendly smile.  I would recommend this restaurant to anyone and feel confident they won’t be disappointed!

I must say. I dont normally eat at places like this, but this establishment is wonderful all the way around the board. Walking in, everybody is super nice. Service is immaculate. The food. God the food. The food quality is so well done. Everytime i come in. I have to get something different, and I've never been disappointed. Not even the slightest. Hats off to the kitchen and the front of the house staff. Most definitely one of the best in louisville. Thank you guys for being there.
Great food, especially the brussel sprout salad! Fantastic service!
